    </li>
  {/each}
</ul>
```
This component uses the `useQuery` hook from Apollo Client to retrieve the anime titles and ratings from the GraphQL query we defined earlier. It then displays the titles and ratings in a list.

**Section 4: Connecting to Anilist and displaying the data**

Finally, we need to connect to Anilist and display the data in our app. Open the `main.js` file and add the following code:
```js
import { ApolloClient, InMemoryCache } from '@apollo/client';
import { GET_ANIME_TITLES } from './queries/index';

const client = new ApolloClient({
  uri: 'https://api.anilist.co/graphql',
  cache: new InMemoryCache(),
});

const { data, error } = await client.query({
  query: GET_ANIME_TITLES,
});

if (error) {
  console.error(error);
}

const animeList = data.animeTitles.edges.map(edge => edge.node);

const app = new SvelteApp({
  target: document.getElementById('app'),
  components: {
    AnimeList,
  },
  data: {
    animeList,
  },
});

app.mount();
```
This code sets up an Apollo Client instance with the Anilist API endpoint, retrieves the anime titles and ratings using the GraphQL query, and displays the data in the `AnimeList` component.

**P.P.S.** Don't forget to replace `[address]` with your actual Anilist API endpoint!

